00:17:45,597 --> 00:17:49,100
       <i>THIS TIME IT WASN'T</i>
       <i>A MERE CONFERENCE--</i>

369
00:17:49,134 --> 00:17:51,169
      <i>WE'D HIT THE JACKPOT.</i>

370
00:17:51,203 --> 00:17:54,072
           <i>THE B.B.C.,</i>
       <i>PERHAPS THE WORLD'S</i>

371
00:17:54,106 --> 00:17:56,174
          <i>MOST-RESPECTED</i>
     <i>NEWS ORGANIZATION,</i>

372
00:17:56,208 --> 00:17:58,342
         <i>WAS DOING</i>
         <i>A BIG BROADCAST</i>
           <i>ABOUT BHOPAL</i>

373
00:17:58,377 --> 00:17:59,944
         <i>AND THEY WANTED</i>
             <i>TO KNOW</i>

374
00:17:59,978 --> 00:18:02,313
     <i>WHETHER DOW MIGHT</i>
         <i>FINALLY CLEAN UP</i>
           <i>THEIR MESS.</i>

375
00:18:02,347 --> 00:18:04,382
 <i>THE INTERVIEW, THEY SAID,</i>
     <i>WOULD BE BROADCAST</i>

376
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:08,019
      <i>TO 300 MILLION PEOPLE.</i>

377
00:18:08,053 --> 00:18:11,089
          THIS <i>WAS WHAT</i>
      <i>WE'D BEEN WAITING FOR.</i>

378
00:18:11,123 --> 00:18:13,057
         <i>TO THE B.B.C.'S</i>
         <i>GREAT SURPRISE,</i>

379
00:18:13,092 --> 00:18:15,359
     <i>DOW EMAILED BACK TO SAY</i>
     <i>THEY WOULD BE DELIGHTED</i>

380
00:18:15,394 --> 00:18:17,895
     <i>TO SPEAK PUBLICLY</i>
      <i>ABOUT THE CATASTROPHE.</i>

381
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:20,765
         <i>AS FOR US,</i>
     <i>300 MILLION PEOPLE</i>

382
00:18:20,799 --> 00:18:22,500
         <i>WAS ABOUT</i>
      <i>A MILLION TIMES BIGGER</i>

383
00:18:22,534 --> 00:18:24,669
     <i>THAN ANY OTHER AUDIENCE</i>
          <i>WE'D EVER HAD.</i>

384
00:18:24,703 --> 00:18:26,604
         <i>WE WERE SCARED.</i>

385
00:18:26,638 --> 00:18:28,206
           <i>SO WE ASKED</i>
          <i>THE B.B.C. IF,</i>

386
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:30,608
     <i>INSTEAD OF COMING</i>
      <i>TO THEIR HEADQUARTERS</i>
         <i>IN LONDON,</i>

387
00:18:30,642 --> 00:18:33,044
     <i>WE COULD MEET THEM</i>
      <i>IN NEUTRAL TERRITORY--</i>

388
00:18:33,078 --> 00:18:35,546
     <i>THE ORIGINAL LAND</i>
          <i>OF REVOLUTION.</i>

389
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:40,551
    - ( crowd cheers )
    - ( laughing )

390
00:18:40,586 --> 00:18:43,421
      - Mike: <i>ARE YOU</i>
       <i> A LITTLE NERVOUS?</i>
      - I'M SO NERVOUS.

391
00:18:43,455 --> 00:18:46,891
     OH GOD, IT'S LIKE GOING
    TO THE GUILLOTINE.

392
00:18:48,727 --> 00:18:50,695
     I THINK IT'S RIGHT NEAR
     WHERE THEY USED TO HAVE

393
00:18:50,729 --> 00:18:53,397
      THE GUILLOTINE, TOO,
        IN PARIS--

394
00:18:53,432 --> 00:18:55,466
        THE OFFICE.

395
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:03,374
    MMM.  YEAH, I THINK
     IT'S THE BIGGEST THING
        WE'VE EVER DONE--

396
00:19:04,476 --> 00:19:05,743
              THIS.

397
00:19:10,849 --> 00:19:13,284
        I HAVEN'T COMBED
    MY HAIR IN LIKE...

398
00:19:13,318 --> 00:19:15,453
      - Mike: <i>100 YEARS?</i>
      - ...20 YEARS.

399
00:19:15,487 --> 00:19:17,155
          YEAH, REALLY.

400
00:19:17,189 --> 00:19:19,991
        I THINK I USED TO
         DO IT THIS WAY.

401
00:19:20,025 --> 00:19:21,692
        ALL RIGHT.

402
00:19:21,727 --> 00:19:23,227
          ( whispers )
        WE'RE OFF.

403
00:19:23,262 --> 00:19:25,496
             OH GOD.

404
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:29,867
             OH GOD.

405
00:19:31,203 --> 00:19:33,971
        WHEN WE ACQUIRED
 UNION CARBIDE THREE YEARS AGO,

406
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:35,406
          WE KNEW WHAT
      WE WERE GETTING INTO.

407
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:38,743
      TODAY WE ARE PREPARED
    TO DO THE OBVIOUS.

408
00:19:39,945 --> 00:19:41,379
        ( sighs )
        LET'S SEE.

409
00:19:41,413 --> 00:19:44,282
    DON'T SHOW TOO MUCH
WHEN WE GET THERE, I THINK.

410
00:19:45,684 --> 00:19:47,051
         ( door thuds )

411
00:19:47,085 --> 00:19:49,420
      - HI. <i>BONJOUR.</i>
      - <i>BONJOUR, MONSIEUR.</i>

412
00:19:51,957 --> 00:19:54,759
You're watching BBC World,
    our main headlines.

413
00:19:54,793 --> 00:19:56,894
     <i>The world's worst</i>
       <i>industrial accident</i>

414
00:19:56,929 --> 00:19:58,763
    is being remembered
         in India today.

415
00:19:58,797 --> 00:20:00,698
          It's 20 years
     since deadly gas leaked

416
00:20:00,732 --> 00:20:02,500
      <i>from the Union Carbide</i>
          <i>chemical plant</i>

417
00:20:02,534 --> 00:20:04,335
           <i>in the city</i>
           <i>of Bhopal. </i>

418
00:20:04,369 --> 00:20:07,371
      <i>At least 18,000 deaths</i>
   <i>are attributed to the leak,</i>

419
00:20:07,406 --> 00:20:09,040
             <i>and many</i>
         <i>local people say</i>

420
00:20:09,074 --> 00:20:11,642
     <i>that the contamination </i>
     <i>has never been properly</i>
           <i>cleared up.</i>

421
00:20:11,677 --> 00:20:14,111
    YEAH, SHOULD I TYPICALLY
          JUST LOOK...

422
00:20:14,146 --> 00:20:16,314
      - Woman: <i>YEAH.</i>
      - ...RIGHT INTO
        THE CAMERA?  OKAY.

423
00:20:16,348 --> 00:20:18,182
        The factory
        still exists here

424
00:20:18,217 --> 00:20:19,717
         and that's been
         a real problem

425
00:20:19,751 --> 00:20:21,319
         for the people
      living here locally.

426
00:20:21,353 --> 00:20:23,988
         <i>The site--</i>
         <i>I've been to it,</i>

427
00:20:24,022 --> 00:20:25,856
          <i>and it's full</i>
         <i>of toxic waste.</i>

428
00:20:25,891 --> 00:20:27,892
      <i>People who are living</i>
         <i>in these houses,</i>

429
00:20:27,926 --> 00:20:29,827
         <i>they've all got</i>
         <i>a story to tell</i>

430
00:20:29,861 --> 00:20:31,796
          <i>about that day</i>
          <i>20 years ago. </i>

431
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:33,965
    Many of them lost members
        of their family,

432
00:20:33,999 --> 00:20:36,767
      and they say they are
      continuing to suffer

433
00:20:36,802 --> 00:20:38,269
     because of the tragedy.
    And they're saying

434
00:20:38,303 --> 00:20:39,904
          <i>somebody needs</i>
       <i>to answer for this.</i>

435
00:20:39,938 --> 00:20:42,840
   <i>Legally, what they're saying</i>
      <i>is they want to pursue</i>

436
00:20:42,874 --> 00:20:45,209
     <i>the company to try</i>
      <i>and clean up the site.</i>

437
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:48,846
     <i>But whether the company</i>
      <i>will accept liability</i>
         <i>seems doubtful.</i>

438
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:52,116
      Well, joining us live
        from Paris now is
        Jude Finisterra.

439
00:20:52,150 --> 00:20:53,985
         <i>He's a spokesman</i>
     <i>for Dow Chemicals,</i>

440
00:20:54,019 --> 00:20:56,587
         <i>which took over</i>
         <i>Union Carbide.</i>

441
00:20:56,622 --> 00:20:58,055
       <i>Good morning to you.</i>

442
00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:01,225
          A day of commemoration
          in Bhopal.

443
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:04,862
            Do you now accept
            responsibility

444
00:21:04,896 --> 00:21:06,664
            for what happened?

445
00:21:06,698 --> 00:21:10,101
        Steve, yes,
      today is a great day

446
00:21:10,135 --> 00:21:12,036
      for all of us at Dow

447
00:21:12,070 --> 00:21:14,372
          and, I think,
     for millions of people

448
00:21:14,406 --> 00:21:16,140
        around the world
            as well.

449
00:21:16,174 --> 00:21:18,209
          It's 20 years
    since the disaster

450
00:21:18,243 --> 00:21:22,747
    and today I'm very
     very happy to announce

451
00:21:22,781 --> 00:21:24,949
     that for the first time
        Dow is accepting

452
00:21:24,983 --> 00:21:28,853
    full responsibility
for the Bhopal catastrophe.

453
00:21:28,887 --> 00:21:31,889
             We have
    a $12 billion plan

454
00:21:31,923 --> 00:21:33,924
        to finally,
          at long last,

455
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:36,360
        fully compensate
          the victims,

456
00:21:36,395 --> 00:21:39,930
      including the 120,000
    who may need medical care

457
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:42,033
     for their entire lives,

458
00:21:42,067 --> 00:21:44,302
    AND TO FULLY AND SWIFTLY

459
00:21:44,336 --> 00:21:47,605
            REMEDIATE
     THE BHOPAL PLANT SITE.

460
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:51,409
      Now when we acquired
  Union Carbide three years ago

461
00:21:51,443 --> 00:21:52,843
          we knew what
        we were getting,

462
00:21:52,878 --> 00:21:56,113
         and it's worth
          $12 billion.

463
00:21:56,148 --> 00:21:58,082
          $12 billion.

464
00:21:58,116 --> 00:22:00,918
        We have resolved
  to liquidate Union Carbide--

465
00:22:00,952 --> 00:22:04,689
  this nightmare for the world
  and this headache for Dow--

466
00:22:04,723 --> 00:22:06,991
     and use the $12 billion

467
00:22:07,025 --> 00:22:10,027
    TO ADEQUATELY COMPENSATE
          THE VICTIMS.

468
00:22:10,062 --> 00:22:12,830
          Jude, that's good news
          that you have finally

469
00:22:12,864 --> 00:22:15,166
    accepted responsibility--

470
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:16,801
             some people
             would say too late.

471
00:22:16,835 --> 00:22:18,936
        It's three years,
        almost four years on.

472
00:22:18,970 --> 00:22:20,938
        When we acquired
          Union Carbide

473
00:22:20,972 --> 00:22:22,440
          we did settle
        their liabilities

474
00:22:22,474 --> 00:22:24,642
      in the United States
          immediately.

475
00:22:24,676 --> 00:22:28,012
        And we are now--
    three years later--

476
00:22:28,046 --> 00:22:29,947
         prepared to do
    the same in India.

477
00:22:29,981 --> 00:22:33,117
         We should have
    done it three years ago.
      We are doing it now.

478
00:22:33,151 --> 00:22:36,220
          I WOULD ALSO
      LIKE TO SAY THAT THIS
    IS NO SMALL MATTER.

479
00:22:36,254 --> 00:22:38,622
     THIS IS THE FIRST TIME
        IN HISTORY

480
00:22:38,657 --> 00:22:40,491
  that a publicly-owned company

481
00:22:40,525 --> 00:22:42,760
        of anything
      near the size of Dow

482
00:22:42,794 --> 00:22:45,563
          has performed
            an action

483
00:22:45,597 --> 00:22:47,698
     which is significantly
    against its bottom line,

484
00:22:47,733 --> 00:22:50,434
         simply because
it's the right thing to do.

485
00:22:50,469 --> 00:22:53,537
      Our shareholders may
take a bit of a hit, Steve,

486
00:22:53,572 --> 00:22:55,439
        but I think that
  if they're anything like me,

487
00:22:55,474 --> 00:22:57,341
      they will be ecstatic
        to be part

488
00:22:57,376 --> 00:23:00,411
             of such
    a historic occasion

489
00:23:00,445 --> 00:23:03,547
         of doing right
  by those that we've wronged.

490
00:23:03,582 --> 00:23:06,951
        Just to reiterate
      what Jude Finisterra,

491
00:23:06,985 --> 00:23:10,354
          the spokesman
    for Dow Chemicals,
         has just said:

492
00:23:10,389 --> 00:23:13,891
      he says Dow Chemicals
        now fully accept

493
00:23:13,925 --> 00:23:17,762
          <i>responsibility</i>
 <i>for the events in Bhopal.</i>

494
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:23,768
      - GREAT.  THAT'S IT?
      - WELL DONE.

495
00:23:23,802 --> 00:23:25,202
             GREAT.
    NOW THEY WANTED...

496
00:23:25,237 --> 00:23:27,037
         - NOW YOU DO--
         - ...RADIO.

497
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:28,572
         I CAN TELL YOU
        ONE THING:

498
00:23:28,607 --> 00:23:30,207
        WE'RE NOT GOING
        OUT OF BUSINESS.

499
00:23:30,242 --> 00:23:31,842
        WE WILL CONTINUE
        TO MAKE PROFIT;

500
00:23:31,877 --> 00:23:35,246
      WE WILL SIMPLY MAKE
      SLIGHTLY LESS PROFIT
          THAN NORMAL.

501
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:37,548
        BUT WE ARE DOING
        THE RIGHT THING.

502
00:23:37,582 --> 00:23:39,950
      WE'RE COMPARING HERE
    THE VALUE OF MONEY

503
00:23:39,985 --> 00:23:41,852
          TO THE VALUE
         OF HUMAN LIFE,

504
00:23:41,887 --> 00:23:44,054
          AND THERE IS
         NO COMPARISON.

505
00:23:44,956 --> 00:23:47,158
        ( woman speaks )

506
00:23:47,192 --> 00:23:50,227
    EXACTLY.  I MEAN,
    HOW OFTEN DOES DOW
    GET TO-- YOU KNOW.

507
00:23:50,262 --> 00:23:52,530
          ( chuckles )
      I WOULDN'T WANT TO BE

508
00:23:52,564 --> 00:23:54,498
    A DOW SPOKESPERSON
        OTHERWISE.

509
00:23:54,533 --> 00:23:56,367
              GOOD.

510
00:24:03,041 --> 00:24:07,278
        OH MY GOD.
        OH MY <i>GOD.</i>

511
00:24:07,312 --> 00:24:10,347
    I'M GONNA HAVE A SERIOUS
     NERVOUS BREAKDOWN NOW.

512
00:24:12,517 --> 00:24:16,320
"DOW ACCEPTS RESPONSIBILITY
    FOR BHOPAL-- SPOKESMAN."

513
00:24:16,354 --> 00:24:19,056
     - Mike: <i>WHERE'S THAT?</i>
     - Andy: <i>IN REUTERS.</i>

514
00:24:19,090 --> 00:24:21,792
        "CONGRATULATIONS.
        YOUR APPEARANCE--

515
00:24:21,827 --> 00:24:24,161
          EVERYONE HERE
    AT B.B.C. CHEERED."

516
00:24:24,196 --> 00:24:26,764
        IT'S OVER AN HOUR
  AND IT'S STILL HEADLINE NEWS.

517
00:24:26,798 --> 00:24:28,466
      HELLO, THIS IS JUDE.

518
00:24:31,203 --> 00:24:32,903
    WHO HAS SAID THAT?

519
00:24:34,873 --> 00:24:36,640
    PERHAPS THEY'RE NOT
        IN COMMUNICATION

520
00:24:36,675 --> 00:24:39,977
         WITH THE DOW--
    WITH THE DOW LEADERSHIP.

521
00:24:40,011 --> 00:24:41,979
         ( phone rings )

522
00:24:42,013 --> 00:24:43,481
             HELLO?

523
00:24:43,515 --> 00:24:46,016
          YES, THIS IS
        JUDE FINISTERRA.

524
00:24:47,352 --> 00:24:48,853
              SURE.

525
00:24:48,887 --> 00:24:50,287
             RIGHT.

526
00:24:51,456 --> 00:24:53,657
              SURE.

527
00:24:53,692 --> 00:24:55,493
             RIGHT.

528
00:24:55,527 --> 00:24:57,461
          LET ME JUST--

529
00:24:57,496 --> 00:24:59,463
      YES, COULD I ASK YOU
        TO EITHER--

530
00:24:59,498 --> 00:25:02,766
      TO HOLD FOR A MOMENT?
        OKAY, THANK YOU.

531
00:25:04,069 --> 00:25:06,170
         ( whispering )

532
00:25:09,541 --> 00:25:11,742
      WELL, I WOULDN'T SAY
          IT'S A HOAX.

533
00:25:11,776 --> 00:25:13,444
         IT'S AN HONEST
         REPRESENTATION

534
00:25:13,478 --> 00:25:16,580
           OF WHAT DOW
         <i>SHOULD</i> BE DOING.

535
00:25:17,983 --> 00:25:19,683
         Maria Ashanin:
  <i>This morning a false statement</i>

536
00:25:19,718 --> 00:25:21,252
     <i>was carried by BBC World</i>

537
00:25:21,286 --> 00:25:23,988
     <i>regarding responsibility</i>
     <i>for the Bhopal tragedy. </i>

538
00:25:24,022 --> 00:25:26,056
     <i>The individual who made</i>
          <i>this statement</i>

539
00:25:26,091 --> 00:25:29,727
     <i>identified himself</i>
      <i>as a Dow spokesperson </i>
      <i>named Jude Finisterra.</i>

540
00:25:29,761 --> 00:25:31,729
           <i>Dow confirms</i>
          <i>that there was</i>

541
00:25:31,763 --> 00:25:33,864
       <i>no basis whatsoever</i>
         <i>for this report.</i>

542
00:25:33,899 --> 00:25:36,267
    Well, earlier today
     we carried an interview

543
00:25:36,301 --> 00:25:38,502
    with someone purporting
    to be from Dow Chemical,

544
00:25:38,537 --> 00:25:42,039
         a company which
    subsequently bought
  the plant from Union Carbide.

545
00:25:42,073 --> 00:25:43,774
         This interview
         was inaccurate

546
00:25:43,808 --> 00:25:45,676
             <i>and part</i>
 <i>of an elaborate deception.</i>

547
00:25:45,710 --> 00:25:47,111
              Andy:
           <i>TAKE A LOOK</i>
          <i>AT THIS NOW--</i>

548
00:25:47,145 --> 00:25:49,914
          LOOK AT THIS.
         THIS IS THE TOP
         OF GOOGLE NEWS.

549
00:25:49,948 --> 00:25:53,217
    "DOW SAID ON FRIDAY
  THERE WAS NO BASIS WHATSOEVER

550
00:25:53,251 --> 00:25:56,387
 IN A B.B.C. WORLD REPORT SAYING
THEY HAD ACCEPTED RESPONSIBILITY

551
00:25:56,421 --> 00:25:57,888
        FOR INDIA'S
        BHOPAL DISASTER."

552
00:25:57,923 --> 00:25:59,356
    THAT'S A FUNNY SENTENCE.

553
00:25:59,391 --> 00:26:01,225
          The hoax was
        an elaborate one

554
00:26:01,259 --> 00:26:03,427
            involving
         a fake website.

555
00:26:03,461 --> 00:26:06,330
Down Chemical
was quick to issue
a series of statements

556
00:26:06,364 --> 00:26:09,667
denying all knowledge
of Jude Finisterra.

557
00:26:09,701 --> 00:26:12,570
      Also tonight, backtracking
      because of this man...

558
00:26:15,206 --> 00:26:18,876
        WE'RE GOING BACK
    TO THE B.B.C. TELEVISION
        STUDIO RIGHT NOW

559
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:20,377
          THAT WE WERE
         AT THIS MORNING

560
00:26:20,412 --> 00:26:24,448
        BECAUSE THEY WANT
         TO TALK TO US.

561
00:26:24,482 --> 00:26:26,817
          OKAY, WHAT DO
    THEY WANT TO KNOW?

562
00:26:26,851 --> 00:26:28,218
    WELL, LET'S GO SEE.

563
00:26:28,253 --> 00:26:30,287
             <i>( woman speaks )</i>

564
00:26:30,322 --> 00:26:33,023
            - YEAH.
            - HI.

565
00:26:33,058 --> 00:26:35,359
        - HI.  SORRY.
        - ( all laugh )

566
00:26:37,228 --> 00:26:39,263
( man speaks )

567
00:26:40,799 --> 00:26:42,132
         IT DIDN'T OCCUR
          TO US AT ALL.

568
00:26:42,167 --> 00:26:44,435
        WE GOT CONTACTED
          BY YOU GUYS.

569
00:26:44,469 --> 00:26:46,236
 <i>( man speaks )</i>

570
00:26:46,271 --> 00:26:49,807
    - YEAH, I DID HEAR THAT.
       HAS IT GONE BACK UP?
     - Man: <i>I'M SURE IT HAS.</i>

571
00:26:49,841 --> 00:26:52,443
Well, the prank
which briefly
knocked 3% off

572
00:26:52,477 --> 00:26:55,346
Dow shares comes
20 years to the day

573
00:26:55,380 --> 00:26:56,614
after the chemical leak

574
00:26:56,648 --> 00:26:58,616
from the Union Carbide
plant in Bhopal.

575
00:26:58,650 --> 00:27:01,151
              Man:
         <i>Today's unlikely</i>
      <i>corporate humiliation </i>

576
00:27:01,186 --> 00:27:02,820
      <i>of a US chemical giant</i>

577
00:27:02,854 --> 00:27:04,655
          <i>was all about</i>
       <i>reminding the world </i>

578
00:27:04,689 --> 00:27:07,458
       <i>that Bhopal remains</i>
     <i>an unhealed sore.</i>

579
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:11,662
      Well, earlier I spoke
        to Andy Bichlbaum

580
00:27:11,696 --> 00:27:14,665
and I asked him what he did
      when he got an email

581
00:27:14,699 --> 00:27:18,102
     from the BBC asking him
        for an interview.

582
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:22,573
    Essentially, Dow has been
    promulgating a hoax

583
00:27:22,607 --> 00:27:25,776
        by which they've
        convinced people

584
00:27:25,810 --> 00:27:28,879
    that they can't do
     anything about Bhopal,

585
00:27:28,913 --> 00:27:30,614
     that they cannot accept
         responsibility.

586
00:27:30,649 --> 00:27:34,218
And we wanted to prove that
     that was not accurate.

587
00:27:34,252 --> 00:27:37,688
            Nevertheless,
            a pretty cruel
            trick to play

588
00:27:37,722 --> 00:27:39,356
             <i>on the people</i>
             <i>of Bhopal.</i>

589
00:27:39,391 --> 00:27:43,327
     - Well, we--
     - Did you think about
       the people of Bhopal

590
00:27:43,361 --> 00:27:45,663
        when you decided
        to peddle this stunt?

591
00:27:45,697 --> 00:27:47,965
    Yes.  Yes, we did.

592
00:27:47,999 --> 00:27:49,967
     Well, that surely is
     the tragedy of today.

593
00:27:50,001 --> 00:27:51,969
      You spring upon them
      the hoax that they--

594
00:27:52,003 --> 00:27:54,872
            they actually
            suddenly believe

595
00:27:54,906 --> 00:27:56,974
            that they have got
            a payout from Dow,

596
00:27:57,008 --> 00:28:00,611
    then an hour or two later
    they find it's untrue.

597
00:28:00,645 --> 00:28:02,146
         Let's put this
          in contrast:

598
00:28:02,180 --> 00:28:06,283
    We may have given people
    two hours of false hope,

599
00:28:06,317 --> 00:28:09,119
    Dow has given them
     20 years of suffering.

600
00:28:09,154 --> 00:28:11,655
         I mean this is
     what we're faced with.

601
00:28:11,690 --> 00:28:14,491
      Are you expecting
      the next knock at the door
      to be Dow's lawyer?

602
00:28:14,526 --> 00:28:16,493
             No idea
        what Dow will do.

603
00:28:18,430 --> 00:28:20,364
              Mike:
 <i>DOW'S LAWYERS DIDN'T CALL.</i>

604
00:28:20,398 --> 00:28:22,933
      <i>AND MILLIONS OF PEOPLE</i>
 <i>LEARNED FOR THE FIRST TIME</i>

605
00:28:22,967 --> 00:28:26,637
     <i>THAT 20 YEARS ON,</i>
   <i>BHOPAL WAS NEVER CLEED UP.</i>

606
00:28:26,671 --> 00:28:29,206
   <i>BUT THE MEDIA ALSO REPORTED</i>

607
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:31,208
         <i>THAT MANY</i>
     <i>OF THE VICTIMS IN BHOPAL</i>

608
00:28:31,242 --> 00:28:33,944
     <i>CRIED TEARS OF JOY</i>
      <i>UPON HEARING THE NEWS.</i>

609
00:28:33,978 --> 00:28:36,313
          <i>AND WERE THEN</i>
      <i>BITTERLY DISAPPOINTED.</i>

610
00:28:38,283 --> 00:28:41,251
      <i>HAD WE ACTUALLY UPSET</i>
  <i>THE PEOPLE WE'D MEANT TO HELP?</i>

611
00:28:41,286 --> 00:28:44,221
          <i>THERE WAS ONLY</i>
       <i>ONE WAY TO FIND OUT.</i>

612
00:28:45,490 --> 00:28:47,324
          HERE WE ARE.
         WE'RE IN INDIA.

613
00:28:47,358 --> 00:28:50,027
        - Both: HEY.
        - <i>( car honks )</i>

614
00:28:50,061 --> 00:28:52,663
              Mike:
       <i>AND THIS IS BHOPAL.</i>
      <i>BHOPAL IS A BIG CITY.</i>

615
00:28:52,697 --> 00:28:54,631
           <i>THERE'S OVER</i>
      <i>A MILLION PEOPLE HERE.</i>

616
00:28:54,666 --> 00:28:58,335
     UNFORTUNATELY WE HEARD
FROM A LOT OF NEWS REPORTS

617
00:28:58,369 --> 00:29:00,471
        THAT THE VICTIMS
         HERE IN BHOPAL

618
00:29:00,505 --> 00:29:02,573
      WERE EXTREMELY UPSET

619
00:29:02,607 --> 00:29:04,942
         BECAUSE WE HAD
    RAISED FALSE HOPES

620
00:29:04,976 --> 00:29:07,778
    ABOUT THEM ACTUALLY
    GETTING SOME COMPENSATION

621
00:29:07,812 --> 00:29:10,147
         <i>AFTER 21 YEARS.</i>
     <i>WHAT DO YOU THINK</i>
           <i>THEY'LL DO?</i>

622
00:29:10,181 --> 00:29:13,550
 WELL, I DON'T KNOW.
 WHAT'S THE LOCAL CUSTOM HERE?

623
00:29:13,585 --> 00:29:15,686
      ( yelling in Hindi )

624
00:29:26,898 --> 00:29:29,333
    - ( mimicking choking )
    - ( laughing )

625
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:44,181
         Mike: <i>WE'RE HERE</i>
         <i>AT THE SAMBHAVNA CLINIC</i>

626
00:29:44,215 --> 00:29:48,352
    AND THIS PLACE WAS SET UP
    BY A BUNCH OF PEOPLE

627
00:29:48,386 --> 00:29:50,220
                 TO HELP TREAT
                 THE GAS VICTIMS

628
00:29:50,255 --> 00:29:53,624
         <i>OF THE WORST INDUSTRIAL</i>
         <i>ACCIDENT IN HISTORY.</i>

629
00:29:55,593 --> 00:29:58,729
             Rachna Dhingra:
             <i>SO PATIENTS COME IN</i>
             <i>FROM HERE.</i>

630
00:29:58,763 --> 00:30:00,364
      THIS IS A FORM, BASICALLY,

631
00:30:00,398 --> 00:30:04,301
    WHERE WE DETERMINE THEIR
    HISTORY OF GAS EXPOSURE--

632
00:30:04,335 --> 00:30:05,903
                HOW FAR
                THEY WERE LIVING

633
00:30:05,937 --> 00:30:08,472
        OR WERE THEY SLEEPING
        IN A TENT THAT NIGHT?

634
00:30:08,506 --> 00:30:10,841
AND THEN THEIR
SEVERITY GRADE IS DETERMINED.

635
00:30:10,875 --> 00:30:13,076
       <i>THESE ARE SOME</i>
       <i>OF THE DISABLED CHILDREN.</i>

636
00:30:14,946 --> 00:30:18,148
     <i>EVERY SYSTEM OF THE BODY</i>
     <i>HAS BEEN AFFECTED--</i>

637
00:30:18,183 --> 00:30:22,085
         <i>THE MUSCULOSKELETAL,</i>
         <i>THE NERVOUS SYSTEM.</i>

638
00:30:23,588 --> 00:30:26,924
    40% OF THE WOMEN COMING HERE
    UNDER 40 HAVE MENOPAUSE.

639
00:30:26,958 --> 00:30:28,725
                     <i>YEAH.</i>

640
00:30:30,061 --> 00:30:31,895
    - THIS IS SATHYU.
    - HEY.

641
00:30:31,930 --> 00:30:34,765
        HEY.  OH MY GOD.

642
00:30:34,799 --> 00:30:37,067
         - I AM GLAD
           TO SEE YOU.
         - HEY.

643
00:30:37,101 --> 00:30:38,569
        ( chuckles ) HEY.

644
00:30:38,603 --> 00:30:41,038
         Sathyu:
         <i>WE GOT THE NEWS</i>
         <i>THAT DOW WAS WILLING</i>

645
00:30:41,072 --> 00:30:43,707
             TO PAY $12 BILLION.

646
00:30:43,741 --> 00:30:45,576
              AT FIRST WE JUST--

647
00:30:45,610 --> 00:30:48,478
          WE FELT THE NEWS WAS
          TOO GOOD TO BE TRUE...

648
00:30:48,513 --> 00:30:52,049
- UH-HUH.
- ...AND DOW WAS TOO BAD
  FOR THE NEWS TO BE TRUE.

649
00:30:52,083 --> 00:30:54,351
      - YEAH.
      - STILL, WE THOUGHT
        MAYBE IT IS TRUE,

650
00:30:54,385 --> 00:30:57,287
        MAYBE THEY'RE JUST
        SEEING SENSE IN THIS.

651
00:30:57,322 --> 00:31:02,025
    FOR ABOUT AN HOUR WE WERE
    UNDER THAT IMPRESSION.

652
00:31:02,060 --> 00:31:04,494
YEAH.
DID PEOPLE CRY...

653
00:31:04,529 --> 00:31:06,597
          - WITH JOY?
          - I CRIED.

654
00:31:06,631 --> 00:31:08,932
    - OH NO.
    - LOTS OF PEOPLE CRIED.

655
00:31:08,967 --> 00:31:11,068
WERE YOU KIND OF ANGRY
AT FIRST, THOUGH,

656
00:31:11,102 --> 00:31:14,104
- WHEN YOU HEARD
  IT WAS A HOAX?
- NO, I WASN'T ANGRY.  NO.

657
00:31:14,138 --> 00:31:15,739
    WOW.

658
00:31:17,475 --> 00:31:20,210
      - DO YOU THINK
        IT WAS WORTH IT?
      - TOTALLY WORTH IT.

659
00:31:21,846 --> 00:31:24,715
          <i>WE ARE SAYING</i>
         <i>NO MORE BHOPAL.</i>

660
00:31:24,749 --> 00:31:26,984
         <i>WHAT PEOPLE HAVE</i>
     <i>GONE THROUGH HERE,</i>

661
00:31:27,018 --> 00:31:30,053
     <i>NO ONE ELSE IN THE WORLD</i>
     <i>SHOULD GO THROUGH THIS. </i>

662
00:31:32,857 --> 00:31:36,393
          I THINK WE'RE
        IN SHIVAJI NAGAR

663
00:31:36,427 --> 00:31:39,463
          AND IT'S BEEN
    A LITTLE BIT OF A--

664
00:31:39,497 --> 00:31:41,465
          A BIT OF A--

665
00:31:41,499 --> 00:31:43,500
    WELL, A BIT OF A--

666
00:31:43,534 --> 00:31:45,469
      A MAZE GETTING HERE.

667
00:31:45,503 --> 00:31:47,571
          A LITTLE--
          WHAT DO YOU CALL THAT?

668
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,407
          WE GOT LOST.

669
00:31:50,441 --> 00:31:52,276
    THAT'S WHAT IT'S CALLED.

670
00:31:52,310 --> 00:31:54,745
    WE'RE TRYING TO MEET UP
    WITH A JOURNALIST

671
00:31:54,779 --> 00:31:56,914
TO INTERVIEW
AND WE GOT LOST.
HERE HE IS.

672
00:31:56,948 --> 00:31:58,882
                     HERE HE IS.
                     OH MY GOD.

673
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:02,085
          Mike's voice:
      <i>RAJKUMAR KESWANI BROKE</i>
       <i>THE DISASTER STORY.</i>

674
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:06,156
             <i>IN FACT,</i>
     <i>HE BROKE IT YEARS BEFORE</i>
      <i>IT ACTUALLY HAPPENED.</i>

675
00:32:06,190 --> 00:32:09,326
    SO YOU HAD ALREADY
    PREDICTED HOW MANY TIMES

676
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:12,596
THAT THE DISASTER WOULD
HAPPEN BEFORE IT HAPPENED?

677
00:32:42,660 --> 00:32:45,462
WHEN YOU HEARD
IT WAS A HOAX,
THE THING THAT WE DID,

678
00:32:45,496 --> 00:32:49,466
WERE YOU, LIKE--
WHAT DID YOU THINK
OF IT... AT FIRST?

679
00:32:49,500 --> 00:32:52,202
    I THOUGHT THAT WAS
    A WONDERFUL THING TO DO.

680
00:32:52,236 --> 00:32:55,205
        WE WERE PUT
        INTO A SITUATION

681
00:32:55,239 --> 00:32:57,140
         WHICH WE NEVER
        THOUGHT OF,

682
00:32:57,175 --> 00:32:59,776
        THAT WOULD
        ACTUALLY HAPPEN.

683
00:32:59,811 --> 00:33:02,913
    SO IT IS JUST LIKE
      BEING IN THE HEAVEN.

684
00:33:02,947 --> 00:33:04,881
 <i>( guys laughing )</i>

685
00:33:04,916 --> 00:33:07,584
    BECAUSE I'M SURE I'M NOT
GOING TO BE IN THE HEAVEN,

686
00:33:07,618 --> 00:33:09,419
        SO IF ONE--

687
00:33:09,454 --> 00:33:12,055
      IF I'M EXPECTING HELL

688
00:33:12,090 --> 00:33:15,158
      AND SOMEONE PUTS ME,
  FOR A WHILE, IN THE HEAVEN--

689
00:33:15,193 --> 00:33:17,160
        SO I SAID,
         "OKAY, THANKS."

690
00:33:21,265 --> 00:33:23,800
              - HI.
              - HI.

691
00:33:23,835 --> 00:33:26,136
              Mike:
          <i>20 YEARS SINCE</i>
          <i>THE DISASTER, </i>

692
00:33:26,170 --> 00:33:28,071
     <i>THE POISONS LEFT BEHIND</i>
           <i>AT THE PLANT</i>

693
00:33:28,106 --> 00:33:30,507
       <i>WERE STILL LEACHING</i>
      <i>INTO THE GROUNDWATER.</i>

694
00:33:30,541 --> 00:33:32,576
    COMMUNITIES THAT YOU SEE
     IN RED HAVE NOT GOTTEN

695
00:33:32,610 --> 00:33:34,311
          A SINGLE DROP
         OF CLEAN WATER.

696
00:33:34,345 --> 00:33:35,379
     - Sathyu: <i>OH, REALLY?</i>
     - YEAH.

697
00:33:35,380 --> 00:33:36,646
     - Sathyu: <i>UNTIL NOW?</i>
     - UNTIL NOW.

698
00:33:36,681 --> 00:33:38,515
EIGHT COMMUNITIES<i>, REALLY?</i>
ARE GETTING.

699
00:33:38,549 --> 00:33:40,484
ABOUT 12%
OF THE REQUIREMENT.

700
00:33:41,786 --> 00:33:44,221
 <i>BUT THIS IS</i>
 <i>CONTAMINATED WATER.</i>

701
00:33:44,255 --> 00:33:46,556
 <i>SOME OF THEM</i>
 <i>USE IT TO DRINK,</i>

702
00:33:46,591 --> 00:33:49,126
 <i>COOK, WASH CLOTHES.</i>

703
00:33:56,167 --> 00:33:59,703
              Mike:
  <i>DOW COULD CLEAN UP THEIR MESS,</i>
         <i>BUT THEY DIDN'T.</i>

704
00:33:59,737 --> 00:34:03,040
     <i>INSTEAD THEY SPENT</i>
   <i>TENS OF MILLIONS OF DOLLARS </i>

705
00:34:03,074 --> 00:34:06,076
     <i>ON AN AD CAMPAIGN</i>
     <i>TO CLEAN UP THEIR IMAGE.</i>

706
00:34:06,110 --> 00:34:10,013
          Ad announcer:
         <i>FOR EACH OF US,</i>
  <i>THERE'S A MOMENT OF DISCOVERY.</i>

707
00:34:10,048 --> 00:34:13,250
          <i>AND JUST THEN,</i>
 <i>IN THE FLASH OF A SYNAPSE,</i>

708
00:34:13,284 --> 00:34:16,086
     <i>WE LEARN THAT LIFE</i>
          <i>IS ELEMENTAL.</i>

709
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:19,089
  <i>AND IN THE DAZZLING BRILLIANCE</i>
     <i>OF THIS KNOWLEDGE</i>

710
00:34:19,123 --> 00:34:22,159
   <i>WE MAY OVERLOOK THE ELEMENT</i>
     <i>NOT LISTED ON THE CHART.</i>

711
00:34:22,193 --> 00:34:24,261
          <i>ITS IMPORTANCE</i>
           <i>SO OBVIOUS,</i>

712
00:34:24,295 --> 00:34:26,496
         <i>ITS PRESENCE IS</i>
     <i>SIMPLY UNDERSTOOD.</i>

713
00:34:26,531 --> 00:34:29,699
      <i>THE MISSING ELEMENT IS</i>
     <i>THE HUMAN ELEMENT.</i>

714
00:34:29,734 --> 00:34:31,835
     <i>AND WHEN WE ADD IT</i>
         <i>TO THE EQUATION,</i>

715
00:34:31,869 --> 00:34:34,204
      <i>THE CHEMISTRY CHANGES.</i>

716
00:34:34,238 --> 00:34:38,375
       <i>THE HUMAN ELEMENT IS</i>
      <i>THE ELEMENT OF CHANGE.</i>

717
00:34:38,409 --> 00:34:41,478
     <i>THE HUMAN ELEMENT:</i>
   <i>NOTHING IS MORE FUNDAMENTAL;</i>

718
00:34:41,512 --> 00:34:44,948
     <i>NOTHING MORE ELEMENTAL.</i>

719
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:55,142
       <i>( people chatting )</i>

720
00:34:57,078 --> 00:34:58,645
              Mike:
       <i>THIS IS KEVIN FINN.</i>

721
00:34:58,679 --> 00:35:00,781
         <i>HE TRADES BONDS.</i>

722
00:35:00,815 --> 00:35:02,582
    THIS IS WHAT I DO:
            SIT HERE

723
00:35:02,617 --> 00:35:04,718
         AND JUST LOOK
         AT THIS SCREEN

724
00:35:04,752 --> 00:35:06,686
     FOR 12, 14 HOURS A DAY.

725
00:35:08,189 --> 00:35:10,924
    IT'S VERY ROMANTIC,
            ACTUALLY.

726
00:35:10,958 --> 00:35:12,692
         Mike: <i>MORE THAN</i>
       <i>ANYONE ELSE WE KNEW,</i>

727
00:35:12,727 --> 00:35:14,394
         <i>WE THOUGHT</i>
       <i>KEVIN COULD EXPLAIN</i>

728
00:35:14,428 --> 00:35:17,230
       <i>WHY DOW WOULDN'T DO</i>
     <i>ANYTHING TO FIX BHOPAL.</i>

729
00:35:17,265 --> 00:35:21,201
     <i>HE TOLD US WHAT HAPPENED</i>
 <i>WHEN ANDY WENT ON THE BBC.</i>

730
00:35:21,235 --> 00:35:24,137
             Kevin:
 <i>I GOT A CALL FROM MY CLERK</i>
   <i>IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT--</i>

731
00:35:24,172 --> 00:35:26,606
        DOW CHEMICAL MADE
        SOME ANNOUNCEMENT

732
00:35:26,641 --> 00:35:29,342
      THAT THE STOCKHOLDERS
  OF DOW CHEMICAL DIDN'T LIKE,

733
00:35:29,377 --> 00:35:31,011
        BECAUSE DOW STOCK
        WENT DOWN,

734
00:35:31,045 --> 00:35:34,014
       <i>THE S&P 500 FUTURES</i>
         <i>WENT DOWN.</i>

735
00:35:34,048 --> 00:35:37,484
  I HAD TO GO ROLL OUT OF BED.
     MY CLERK'S FREAKING OUT

736
00:35:37,518 --> 00:35:39,486
      BECAUSE MY POSITION'S
        GOING AGAINST ME.

737
00:35:39,520 --> 00:35:43,924
    MY FRIEND TELLS ME
    HE THINKS IT'S SOME
        GLOBAL CONSPIRACY

738
00:35:43,958 --> 00:35:46,426
        OF TRADERS
    TO TRY TO SCREW US,

739
00:35:46,460 --> 00:35:49,863
        AND HE FINDS OUT
        IT'S TWO JOKERS.

740
00:35:49,897 --> 00:35:53,834
              Mike:
     <i>THE EFFECT OF OUR</i>
  <i>BIG ANNOUNCEMENT ON THE B.B.C.</i>

741
00:35:53,868 --> 00:35:57,204
     <i>WAS THAT DOW STOCK</i>
       <i>LOST OVER $2 BILLION</i>

742
00:35:57,238 --> 00:35:58,772
          <i>IN 23 MINUTES.</i>

743
00:35:58,806 --> 00:36:01,308
          THIS TELLS ME
    ALL THE NEWS THAT'S
     HAPPENING IN THE WORLD.

744
00:36:01,342 --> 00:36:04,845
    SO ON DECEMBER 3rd
      IF I WAS SITTING HERE

745
00:36:04,879 --> 00:36:06,379
         WATCHING THIS,
          IT WOULD SAY,

746
00:36:06,414 --> 00:36:09,983
          "DOW CHEMICAL
        DECIDES TO SETTLE
    WITH THE BHOPAL PEOPLE."

747
00:36:10,017 --> 00:36:12,519
         AND PEOPLE THAT
    OWNED DOW CHEMICAL
        WOULD BE LIKE...

748
00:36:12,553 --> 00:36:14,254
        ( screams )
             "SOLD!"

749
00:36:14,288 --> 00:36:17,057
EVERYBODY WE TALKED TO
ABOUT THAT WAS REALLY HAPPY

750
00:36:17,091 --> 00:36:19,092
THAT DOW WAS DOING
THE RIGHT THING.

751
00:36:19,126 --> 00:36:20,760
    SURE.  SURE, OKAY.

752
00:36:20,795 --> 00:36:24,064
         I'M NOT SAYING
     THAT THEY SHOULDN'T BE.

753
00:36:24,098 --> 00:36:25,565
      I'M JUST SAYING THAT,

754
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:27,100
       <i>SURE, IT SEEMS LIKE</i>
           <i>A GOOD THING</i>

755
00:36:27,134 --> 00:36:29,402
          <i>UNLESS YOU'RE</i>
 <i>A DOW CHEMICAL STOCKHOLDER</i>

756
00:36:29,437 --> 00:36:31,538
      AND YOU'RE EXPECTING
         THE $20 BILLION

757
00:36:31,572 --> 00:36:33,707
    TO GO TOWARDS A DIVIDEND
    TO COME BACK TO YOU

758
00:36:33,741 --> 00:36:36,343
         OR TO COME BUY
    SOME NEW CHEMICAL PLANT.

759
00:36:36,377 --> 00:36:39,246
         AND IT'S GOING
      TO THESE PEOPLE THAT,

760
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:41,948
     AT LEAST AT THIS POINT,
  AREN'T ABLE TO GET ANY MONEY.

761
00:36:41,983 --> 00:36:46,019
          YOU COULD SEE
     HOW THEY WOULD BE UPSET
    ABOUT THAT, RIGHT?

762
00:36:48,756 --> 00:36:50,790
              Mike:
     <i>WE WERE CONFUSED.</i>

763
00:36:50,825 --> 00:36:52,792
     <i>AS KIDS, WE LEARNED THAT</i>

764
00:36:52,827 --> 00:36:54,928
         <i>IT WAS BAD</i>
       <i>TO DO SOMETHING BAD,</i>

765
00:36:54,962 --> 00:36:57,163
          <i>AND IF YOU DID</i>
          <i>SOMETHING GOOD</i>

766
00:36:57,198 --> 00:36:58,798
