THIS IS ACTUALLY TRUTH-TELLING
WHERE NORMALLY THERE
WOULD ONLY BE LIES.

1460
01:13:41,900 --> 01:13:44,402
      <i>( jazz band playing )</i>

1461
01:13:47,139 --> 01:13:50,741
HOW DIFFICULT WOULD IT BE
TO REMEDIATE WHAT YOU
SEE HERE TODAY

1462
01:13:50,776 --> 01:13:53,244
AND MAKE IT INHABITABLE,
SAY, NEXT WEEK?

1463
01:13:54,613 --> 01:13:56,948
    JUST TAKE OFF THE--
    TAKE OFF THE COVERS HERE.

1464
01:13:56,982 --> 01:13:58,916
OH YEAH, THAT'S
A GOOD START, YEAH?

1465
01:13:58,951 --> 01:14:00,384
         - ABSOLUTELY.
         - THAT'S IT.

1466
01:14:00,419 --> 01:14:02,587
             FINALLY
      WE WILL BE REOPENING

1467
01:14:02,621 --> 01:14:04,856
         PUBLIC HOUSING
    FOR THE RESIDENTS--

1468
01:14:04,890 --> 01:14:07,458
        FOR THE WORKFORCE
  THAT'S GOING TO MOVE BACK IN

1469
01:14:07,493 --> 01:14:10,027
        AND AGAIN REBUILD
          NEW ORLEANS.

1470
01:14:10,062 --> 01:14:12,163
     Sick, twisted, cruel--

1471
01:14:12,197 --> 01:14:14,565
    those are all words used
      to describe the prank

1472
01:14:14,600 --> 01:14:17,335
     on Louisiana officials
and about 1,000 contractors

1473
01:14:17,369 --> 01:14:18,536
      in New Orleans today.

1474
01:14:18,570 --> 01:14:21,439
        I'm deputy
      assistant secretary,

1475
01:14:21,473 --> 01:14:23,875
     to-- of the assistant,

1476
01:14:23,909 --> 01:14:26,644
    essentially, of Secretary
        Alphonso Jackson.

1477
01:14:26,678 --> 01:14:30,248
            Reporter:
  <i>Rene Oswin can't get his title</i>
 <i>right or his relationship</i>

1478
01:14:30,282 --> 01:14:32,283
     <i>to HUD secretary </i>
     <i>Alphonso Jackson.</i>

1479
01:14:32,317 --> 01:14:34,752
          ( cheering )

1480
01:14:34,786 --> 01:14:37,421
           <i>After taking</i>
      <i>the mayor for a ride,</i>

1481
01:14:37,456 --> 01:14:40,424
  <i>these contractors followed him</i>
  <i>to a makeshift ribbon cutting</i>

1482
01:14:40,459 --> 01:14:42,293
          <i>at the Lafitte</i>
         <i>Housing Project.</i>

1483
01:14:42,327 --> 01:14:44,462
Mr. Oswin, you're not even
on the directory of HUD.

1484
01:14:44,496 --> 01:14:46,731
You're not even listed--
don't have a phone number.

1485
01:14:46,765 --> 01:14:49,267
              It's come to that,
              has it?

1486
01:14:49,301 --> 01:14:53,604
        It's come to that.
        Thanks for being the one
        to break the news.

1487
01:14:53,639 --> 01:14:56,007
        HANO, the Housing
    Authority of New Orleans

1488
01:14:56,041 --> 01:14:58,009
    says this is simply
    a cruel cruel joke,

1489
01:14:58,043 --> 01:15:00,545
      trying to give people
     some kind of fake hope

1490
01:15:00,579 --> 01:15:02,680
that they were going to be
    able to move back.

1491
01:15:02,714 --> 01:15:04,815
         <i>( man speaking )</i>

1492
01:15:20,732 --> 01:15:22,400
            ...THIS WHOLE
            PRESS CONFERENCE.

1493
01:15:22,434 --> 01:15:24,869
        I GUESS IT'S JUST
    TO CALL THEIR HAND.

1494
01:15:24,903 --> 01:15:28,206
      I RESPECT THIS HOAX,
    BECAUSE MAYBE IT'LL TAKE
        A HOAX LIKE THIS

1495
01:15:28,240 --> 01:15:31,209
     TO BRING THEM OUT HERE
        TO SEE WHAT WE'RE
         GOING THROUGH.

1496
01:15:31,243 --> 01:15:33,377
SO IF THE HOAX WHAT IT BE,
     A HOAX IS WHAT WE GOT.

1497
01:15:33,412 --> 01:15:36,280
        AND I AIN'T MAD.
        I'M GRABBING ME
         SOME BARBECUE.

1498
01:15:38,483 --> 01:15:40,918
            Juakali:
           <i>I THINK WHAT</i>
         <i>YOU GUYS EXPOSED</i>

1499
01:15:40,953 --> 01:15:43,421
      IS THE FACT THAT HUD
COULD DO THESE GREAT THINGS

1500
01:15:43,455 --> 01:15:45,189
    IF THEY WANTED TO.

1501
01:15:45,224 --> 01:15:48,059
        SECONDLY, YOU GOT
 THE ATTENTION OF THE RESIDENTS

1502
01:15:48,093 --> 01:15:50,228
      SO NOW THEY'RE GONNA
          BEGIN TO ASK,

1503
01:15:50,262 --> 01:15:52,496
      <i>"WELL, WHY AREN'T YOU</i>
      <i>DOING THESE THINGS?" </i>

1504
01:15:52,531 --> 01:15:55,333
     <i>AND NUMBER THREE,</i>
  <i>YOU'RE CREATING A CONTROVERSY</i>

1505
01:15:55,367 --> 01:15:59,370
    TO FEED OFF, TO ORGANIZE
    AND TO BUILD A STRUGGLE

1506
01:15:59,404 --> 01:16:00,972
    TO THE NEXT LEVEL.

1507
01:16:01,006 --> 01:16:03,407
        SO IN MY OPINION,
      EVERYTHING Y'ALL DID

1508
01:16:03,442 --> 01:16:04,842
         WAS EXCELLENT.

1509
01:16:14,786 --> 01:16:16,454
              Mike:
   <i>IT HAD ALL BEEN WORTHWHILE.</i>

1510
01:16:16,488 --> 01:16:19,790
             <i>WE WERE</i>
       <i>ON TOP OF THE WORLD.</i>

1511
01:16:19,825 --> 01:16:23,661
      <i>BUT THEN REALITY BEGAN</i>
           <i>TO SINK IN.</i>

1512
01:16:29,167 --> 01:16:30,801
       <i>WE'D MADE A SPLASH,</i>

1513
01:16:30,836 --> 01:16:33,104
          <i>BUT WE HADN'T</i>
         <i>FIXED THE WORLD.</i>

1514
01:16:33,138 --> 01:16:36,941
 <i>THE FREE MARKET WAS STILL</i>
     <i>DESTROYING NEW ORLEANS.</i>

1515
01:16:40,312 --> 01:16:43,881
       <i>ALL OVER THE WORLD,</i>
 <i>PEOPLE WERE LOSING THEIR HOMES.</i>

1516
01:16:46,885 --> 01:16:48,953
       <i>CLIMATE CHANGE KEPT</i>
          <i>GETTING WORSE.</i>

1517
01:16:52,691 --> 01:16:56,694
          <i>AND IN BHOPAL,</i>
   <i>PEOPLE CONTINUED TO SUFFER.</i>

1518
01:17:03,368 --> 01:17:06,003
     <i>WE REALLY DID NEED</i>
     <i>TO FIX THE WORLD. </i>

1519
01:17:06,038 --> 01:17:08,673
      <i>BUT IT WAS GONNA TAKE</i>
     <i>MORE THAN TWO GUYS</i>

1520
01:17:08,707 --> 01:17:11,075
         <i>WITH CHEAP SUITS</i>
     <i>AND FAKE WEBSITES.</i>

1521
01:17:13,445 --> 01:17:15,713
          <i>IT WOULD TAKE</i>
         <i>MILLIONS OF US.</i>

1522
01:17:19,951 --> 01:17:22,520
     ( shouting in French )

1523
01:17:29,695 --> 01:17:32,730
              Mike:
     <i>BUT EVEN AS OLD REGIMES</i>
         <i>WERE SWEPT AWAY,</i>

1524
01:17:32,764 --> 01:17:35,333
     <i>WE KNEW THAT REAL CHANGE</i>
       <i>WOULDN'T COME EASY.</i>

1525
01:17:36,902 --> 01:17:40,137
         <i>AFTER ALL,</i>
       <i>THE FREE-MARKET CULT</i>
         <i>WAS STILL HERE.</i>

1526
01:17:40,172 --> 01:17:41,505
        - WEALTH.
        - MONEY.

1527
01:17:41,540 --> 01:17:42,540
        - PRIVATIZATION.
        - WEALTH.

1528
01:17:42,574 --> 01:17:43,607
         - MONEY.
         - FREE MARKETS.

1529
01:17:43,642 --> 01:17:45,109
        - PRIVATIZATION.
        - OWNERSHIP.

1530
01:17:45,143 --> 01:17:48,045
     A GREAT DEAL OF MONEY.
     NOW WE CAN AFFORD THAT.

1531
01:17:49,915 --> 01:17:51,615
              Mike:
       <i>REMEMBER THESE GUYS?</i>

1532
01:17:51,650 --> 01:17:53,818
     <i>THEY'RE NOT GOING AWAY.</i>

1533
01:17:53,852 --> 01:17:56,253
      <i>AND NEITHER WOULD WE.</i>

1534
01:18:01,293 --> 01:18:04,095
     <i>WE NEEDED A REALLY</i>
         <i>AMBITIOUS PLAN,</i>

1535
01:18:04,129 --> 01:18:06,731
     <i>BECAUSE ALL WE EVER READ</i>
     <i>IN THE NEWSPAPERS</i>

1536
01:18:06,765 --> 01:18:09,667
     <i>WAS HOW WE NEEDED TO PUT</i>
 <i>EVERYTHING BACK ON TRACK,</i>

1537
01:18:09,701 --> 01:18:12,703
     <i>BACK TO HOW IT WAS</i>
      <i>BEFORE IT FELL APART.</i>

1538
01:18:14,139 --> 01:18:16,974
          <i>BUT HOW IT WAS</i>
         <i>WAS THE PROBLEM.</i>

1539
01:18:17,008 --> 01:18:20,511
      <i>WE NEEDED TO SHOW WHAT</i>
   <i>REAL CHANGE COULD LOOK LIKE.</i>

1540
01:18:23,348 --> 01:18:25,716
     <i>SO TOGETHER WITH A WHOLE</i>
         <i>LOT OF FRIENDS,</i>

1541
01:18:25,751 --> 01:18:28,686
 <i>WE WOULD BLANKET MANHATTAN</i>
       <i>WITH 100,000 COPIES</i>

1542
01:18:28,720 --> 01:18:31,088
 <i>OF OUR VERY OWN NEWSPAPER.</i>

1543
01:18:31,123 --> 01:18:33,924
           <i>WE'D CALL IT</i>
      <i>"THE NEW YORK TIMES."</i>

1544
01:18:35,794 --> 01:18:38,896
   <i>EXCEPT OUR "NEW YORK TIMES"</i>
      <i>WOULD BE A LITTLE BIT</i>
         <i>DIFFERENT.</i>

1545
01:18:41,333 --> 01:18:43,901
   <i>OURS WOULD BE SET SIX MONTHS</i>
          <i>IN THE FUTURE.</i>

1546
01:18:43,935 --> 01:18:46,137
     <i>IT WOULD SHOW WHAT</i>
           <i>COULD HAPPEN</i>

1547
01:18:46,171 --> 01:18:48,906
         <i>IF WE SET</i>
      <i>OUR IMAGINATION FREE.</i>

1548
01:18:55,647 --> 01:18:57,948
        THINGS HAVE
        GOTTEN PRETTY BAD
        AND I THINK IT'S HARD

1549
01:18:57,983 --> 01:19:00,351
        FOR PEOPLE TO IMAGINE
        THE WORLD WORKING
        ANOTHER WAY.

1550
01:19:00,385 --> 01:19:02,653
        SO WE'RE TRYING TO,
        AS REALISTICALLY
        AS POSSIBLE,

1551
01:19:02,687 --> 01:19:04,822
             PRESENT THIS WORLD
             AS IT COULD BE.

1552
01:19:04,856 --> 01:19:09,460
              Andy:
       <i>THEY JUST BROUGHT UP</i>
         <i>THE PROOF</i>

1553
01:19:09,494 --> 01:19:13,664
 OF "THE NEW YORK TIMES" AND IT
  LOOKS UN-FUCKING-BELIEVABLE.

1554
01:19:13,698 --> 01:19:15,633
 <i>REALLY GOOD.</i>

1555
01:19:25,710 --> 01:19:28,579
      The obvious question:
how the heck did you do it?

1556
01:19:28,613 --> 01:19:31,081
     Andy, do you want to start?
     How long were you working
     on this thing

1557
01:19:31,116 --> 01:19:34,285
 - and how many of you?
 - There were a lot of us.
   It wasn't just the Yes Men.

1558
01:19:34,319 --> 01:19:37,488
It was a large group of people.
We were just one of many groups.

1559
01:19:37,522 --> 01:19:40,124
   <i>It was an idea that sparked</i>
 <i>a lot of people's imaginations.</i>

1560
01:19:40,158 --> 01:19:41,992
           <i>They wanted</i>
       <i>to see this happen.</i>

1561
01:19:42,027 --> 01:19:44,361
 And that's sort of the message
     of the paper as well--

1562
01:19:44,396 --> 01:19:47,364
        is "Great.
        We elected Obama
      and that's fantastic,

1563
01:19:47,399 --> 01:19:48,999
      <i>but now the real work</i>
             <i>begins."</i>

1564
01:19:49,034 --> 01:19:51,268
              Mike:
     <i>The idea was to put out</i>
  <i>something that was optimistic,</i>

1565
01:19:51,303 --> 01:19:53,704
       <i>that says we can do</i>
     <i>all these things.</i>
             <i>Why not?</i>

1566
01:19:53,738 --> 01:19:56,874
  We created the system that we
have now, so why not create
    a good one instead?

1567
01:19:56,908 --> 01:19:59,643
      - WOW, VERY GOOD.
      - LET ME TIE YOU UP.

1568
01:19:59,678 --> 01:20:02,346
     - THIS IS THE BIG DAY.
     - <i>"NEW YORK TIMES."</i>

1569
01:20:02,380 --> 01:20:05,216
      7:00 A.M. RUSH HOUR,
        THIS IS THE TIME

1570
01:20:05,250 --> 01:20:06,517
        TO GET THE PAPERS
        OUT THERE.

1571
01:20:06,551 --> 01:20:09,119
- MORNING. FREE "TIMES."
- Woman: <i>FREE "NEW YORK TIMES."</i>

1572
01:20:09,154 --> 01:20:11,388
SPECIAL ISSUE.
SPECIAL ISSUE.

1573
01:20:11,423 --> 01:20:13,691
        "NEW YORK TIMES,"
     FREE "NEW YORK TIMES."

1574
01:20:13,725 --> 01:20:15,860
         SPECIAL EDITION
    OF "THE NEW YORK TIMES."

1575
01:20:18,597 --> 01:20:19,930
              Man:
      <i>FREE "NEW YORK TIMES."</i>

1576
01:20:19,965 --> 01:20:21,832
          IS THIS REAL?

1577
01:20:21,867 --> 01:20:24,602
     - IT'S FAKE, RIGHT?
     - WHO PUBLISHES THIS?

1578
01:20:24,636 --> 01:20:27,037
        CAN I GRAB
      ANOTHER ONE OF THESE?

1579
01:20:27,072 --> 01:20:28,906
             - WHAT?
             - WHAT?

1580
01:20:30,208 --> 01:20:32,209
"NATIONAL HEALTH INSURANCE
ACT PASSES."

1581
01:20:32,244 --> 01:20:34,879
       <i>SO THE PATRIOT--</i>
       <i>THE PATRIOT ACT REPEALED.</i>

1582
01:20:34,913 --> 01:20:37,014
             Woman:
   <i>"MAXIMUM WAGE LAW SUCCEEDS."</i>

1583
01:20:37,048 --> 01:20:38,549
    GOOD LUCK WITH THAT ONE.

1584
01:20:38,583 --> 01:20:42,920
  THIS IS TOO GOOD TO BE TRUE.
BUT... IT'S NOT IMPOSSIBLE.

1585
01:20:42,954 --> 01:20:44,722
IT'S A DREAM NEWSPAPER.

1586
01:20:44,756 --> 01:20:46,524
     <i>RIGHT?</i>

1587
01:20:46,558 --> 01:20:49,793
 <i>IT'S LIKE YOU WAKE UP AND ALL</i>
 <i>THE THINGS THAT YOU WANTED</i>

1588
01:20:49,828 --> 01:20:51,795
    BECAME THE NEWS.

1589
01:20:51,830 --> 01:20:54,365
         THE WAR'S OVER!

1590
01:20:54,399 --> 01:20:56,467
              Mike:
     <i>OUR FAKE NEWS WAS A HIT.</i>

1591
01:20:56,501 --> 01:20:58,269
NEWSPAPER!
NEWS FROM THE FUTURE.

1592
01:20:58,303 --> 01:21:00,938
     <i>BUT WOULD THE REAL NEWS</i>
           <i>PICK IT UP?</i>

1593
01:21:00,972 --> 01:21:04,174
YOU DON'T WORK
FOR "THE NEW YORK TIMES."
WHO IS IT THAT YOU WORK FOR

1594
01:21:04,209 --> 01:21:06,544
- HANDING THIS OUT?
- A GUY NAMED JOHN-- JOHN SMITH.

1595
01:21:06,578 --> 01:21:08,345
      - YEAH, JOHN SMITH.
      - JOHN SMITH?

1596
01:21:08,380 --> 01:21:11,515
    IT'S "THE NEW YORK TIMES,"
    SPECIAL EDITION.  IS THERE
    ANYTHING WRONG WITH IT?

1597
01:21:11,550 --> 01:21:14,018
YEAH, IT'S NOT
"THE NEW YORK TIMES."

1598
01:21:14,052 --> 01:21:15,519
     <i>Read all about it.</i>

1599
01:21:15,554 --> 01:21:19,089
  <i>"The New York Times" declares</i>
     <i>the war in Iraq is over.</i>

1600
01:21:19,124 --> 01:21:22,393
Some commuters got
their hands on what
looks like a special edition

1601
01:21:22,427 --> 01:21:24,828
of "The New York Times."
As you might have
guessed though,

1602
01:21:24,863 --> 01:21:27,932
     - <i>it's a fake.</i>
     - ( speaking German )

1603
01:21:30,135 --> 01:21:32,202
      ( speaking Russian )

1604
01:21:34,739 --> 01:21:39,176
    We printed a paper
    with the headlines
     that we'd like to see.

1605
01:21:39,210 --> 01:21:41,178
        So if these were
          the headlines

1606
01:21:41,212 --> 01:21:43,814
that people were so excited
      to read this morning,

1607
01:21:43,848 --> 01:21:45,416
     let's make them happen.

1608
01:21:45,450 --> 01:21:47,952
           Lili Taylor:
         <i>WE'RE GONNA HAVE</i>
     <i>TO EXERCISE SOME MUSCLES</i>

1609
01:21:47,986 --> 01:21:50,554
    THAT WE EITHER DON'T HAVE
     OR THAT HAVE ATROPHIED.

1610
01:21:50,589 --> 01:21:52,489
         OR SOMETHING--
         A CIVIC MUSCLE,

1611
01:21:52,524 --> 01:21:54,992
     <i>A THRIFTY MUSCLE, </i>
     <i>A GENEROUS MUSCLE.</i>

1612
01:21:55,026 --> 01:21:58,228
         Medea Benjamin:
      <i>WE'VE GOT TO TAKE BACK</i>
         <i>OUR GOVERNMENT.</i>

1613
01:21:58,263 --> 01:22:01,365
  MARCH INTO CITY HALL AND SAY,
"HERE, WE'VE GOT T SOLUTIONS."

1614
01:22:01,399 --> 01:22:05,436
       Frances Fox Piven:
       <i>WE CAN THINK OF THE</i>
          <i>DIFFERENT WAYS</i>

1615
01:22:05,470 --> 01:22:09,039
     THAT WE CAN CONTRIBUTE
     TO A MOVEMENT THAT SAYS

1616
01:22:09,074 --> 01:22:12,176
        BUSINESS AS USUAL
        IS UNACCEPTABLE,

1617
01:22:12,210 --> 01:22:14,511
          <i>BECAUSE PEOPLE</i>
          <i>ARE BEING HURT</i>

1618
01:22:14,546 --> 01:22:17,147
       <i>AND WE'RE NOT GOING</i>
     <i>TO PLAY THE ROLE--</i>

1619
01:22:17,182 --> 01:22:20,050
        THE SUBSERVIENT,
          ROUTINE ROLE

1620
01:22:20,085 --> 01:22:22,019
      THAT WE USUALLY PLAY.

1621
01:22:22,053 --> 01:22:24,488
  - LET'S GO!
  - WE'RE GOING, WE'RE GOING.

1622
01:22:26,057 --> 01:22:28,125
          ( cheering )

1623
01:22:31,162 --> 01:22:35,699
MAKE CHANGE HAPPEN.
PUT YOUR EFFORT ON THE LINE
TO MAKE SOMETHING HAPPEN.

1624
01:22:35,734 --> 01:22:37,868
AND THAT'S WHAT,
KINDA, WE DID HERE.

1625
01:22:37,902 --> 01:22:40,537
AND, YOU KNOW, MAYBE--
IT'S WHAT...

1626
01:22:40,572 --> 01:22:42,439
YEAH, IT'S KIND OF, YEAH.

1627
01:22:42,474 --> 01:22:44,408
      - OH BOY!
      - NO, I KNOW, YEAH!

1628
01:22:44,442 --> 01:22:48,345
            AND IF A FEW PEOPLE
            AT THE TOP CAN MAKE
            THE BAD NEWS HAPPEN,

1629
01:22:48,380 --> 01:22:50,581
             THEN WHY CAN'T ALL
             OF US AT THE BOTTOM

1630
01:22:50,615 --> 01:22:53,617
          <i>GET TOGETHER</i>
          <i>AND MAKE THE GOOD NEWS</i>
          <i>HAPPEN FOR A CHANGE?</i>

1631
01:22:53,652 --> 01:22:55,052
              <i>I MEAN, FOR REAL?</i>

1632
01:23:16,241 --> 01:23:18,876
 <i>( big band music playing )</i>

